FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781046185
OL,3,CCosmic Kiss: Exact time to see rare
OL,4,Cmoment planets come together in night
OL,5,Csky
OL,7,FA Cosmic Kiss is a planetary
OL,8,Fconjunction - an astronomical event
OL,9,Fwhere two or more planets appear
OL,10,Fexceptionally close to one another in
OL,11,Fthe night sky from our perspective on
OL,12,FEarth.
OL,14,FPlanetary conjunctions are an optical
OL,15,Fillusion caused by perspective.
OL,17,FThe planets in our solar system all
OL,18,Forbit the Sun in roughly the same flat
OL,19,Fplane.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781046185
OL,3,CCosmic Kiss: Exact time to see rare
OL,4,Cmoment planets come together in night
OL,5,Csky
OL,7,FAs each planet travels at a different
OL,8,Fspeed, they occasionally line up on
OL,9,Fthe same side of the Sun.
OL,11,FWhen this occurs, the planets appear
OL,12,Fgrouped together in the sky with the
OL,13,Fline of sight from Earth, even if they
OL,14,Fare millions and billions of miles
OL,15,Fapart in space.
OL,17,FIt's all about set up, alignment and
OL,18,Fillusion.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781046185
OL,3,CCosmic Kiss: Exact time to see rare
OL,4,Cmoment planets come together in night
OL,5,Csky
OL,7,FThis week - and most specifically on
OL,8,FTuesday night - Venus and Jupiter will
OL,9,Fbe in conjunction.
OL,11,FThese are the two brightest planets in
OL,12,Four night sky and one of the most
OL,13,Feasily visible astronomical viewings
OL,14,Fof the year.
OL,16,FWhy is it called a Cosmic Kiss?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781046185
OL,3,CCosmic Kiss: Exact time to see rare
OL,4,Cmoment planets come together in night
OL,5,Csky
OL,7,FVenus and Jupiter are the two
OL,8,Fbrightest planets in our solar system
OL,9,Fso their close visual alignment
OL,10,Fcreates the illusion that they will be
OL,11,Fgently close before moving along their
OL,12,Fseparate orbits.
OL,14,FIt's all a bit touch-and-go or a
OL,15,Ffleeting moment.
OL,17,F'Cosmic Kiss' is a description to this
OL,18,Falignment - a nickname if you like.
OL,20,FHow best to view it?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781046185
OL,3,CCosmic Kiss: Exact time to see rare
OL,4,Cmoment planets come together in night
OL,5,Csky
OL,7,FIt's best to see this sparkling planet
OL,8,Fview by looking west around 45 minutes
OL,9,Fafter sunset.
OL,11,FThis year's event coincides with some
OL,12,Fof the latest sunsets of the year,
OL,13,Fwith the Summer Solstice just around
OL,14,Fthe corner.
OL,16,FIdeally, viewing should be done away
OL,17,Ffrom the light pollution of big cities
OL,18,F- and within two hours of sundown.
OL,20,FIt will be visible with the naked eye
OL,21,Fin rural areas with the darkest skies.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781046185
OL,3,CCosmic Kiss: Exact time to see rare
OL,4,Cmoment planets come together in night
OL,5,Csky
OL,7,FClear and cloudless skies will also
OL,8,Fhelp visibility; areas further east
OL,9,Fwill have a better chance of such
OL,10,Fconditions after dark.
OL,12,FHow rare is a Cosmic Kiss?
OL,14,FVenus and Jupiter align about every 10-
OL,15,F15 months, so on average about once a
OL,16,Fyear.
OL,18,FThis month also marks a 'Planet
OL,19,FParade' from June 11 to 15, when
OL,20,FVenus, Jupiter, and Mercury align in
OL,21,Fthe evening sky.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781046185
OL,3,CCosmic Kiss: Exact time to see rare
OL,4,Cmoment planets come together in night
OL,5,Csky
OL,7,FAll three planets will be visible
OL,8,Fwithout a telescope, gathering in the
OL,9,Fsame field of vision.
OL,11,FJust after this point around, June 16-
OL,12,F17, a crescent Moon will join the line
OL,13,Fup - creating a unique photo
OL,14,Fopportunity.
OL,16,FCome the end of the year, another
OL,17,Fmajor alignment of six planets: Mars,
OL,18,FUranus, Saturn and Neptune, is
OL,19,Fexpected to create another striking
OL,20,Fvision in the night sky in early
OL,21,FDecember.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
